				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203975" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1520361464 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">06 Mar 2018 18:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3730350">
									

<blockquote>
<p>MARLEY was dead: to begin with. &#8230; There is no doubt that Marley was dead. This must be distinctly understood, or nothing wonderful can come of the story I am going to relate.<br />
&#8212; Charles Dickens, <em>A Christmas Carol</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>This begins the story of the secret army of the Foundation's restless dead and their desperate and unknown fight to save independent human thought.</p>
<p>If you haven't read <a href="/scp-2111">SCP-2111</a>, wherein Mobile Task Force Omega-Zero (&quot;Ará Orún&quot;) was first introduced, then this may make little sense. Additionally this tale occurs in parallel to <a href="/case-colourless-green">CASE COLOURLESS GREEN</a> and <a href="/your-last-first-day">Your Last First Day</a> the penultimate and final installments of <em>There is No Antimemetics Division</em> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;">qntm</a></span>, which may be found in its entirety at the <a href="/antimemetics-division-hub">Antimemetics Division Hub</a>.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Credits&nbsp;Where&nbsp;Due</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Lyn Marness and Marion Wheeler were created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;">qntm</a></span> and may be found in the Antimemetics Division material linked above.</li>
<li>Santosh Desai was created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;">A Random Day</a></span> and may be found in the <a href="/third-law-hub">Third Law</a> tale <a href="/moonlighting">Moonlighting</a> and the <a href="/resurrection">Resurrection</a> tale <a href="/i-thought-you-died-alone">I Thought You Died Alone</a></li>
<li>Zoe Smith was created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/myriad" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(101948); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=101948&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="Myriad" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=101948)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/myriad" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(101948); return false;">Myriad</a></span> in <a href="/scp-1638">SCP-1638</a> and the silence left in her absence is loudly heard in the <a href="/on-mount-golgotha-hub">On Mount Golgotha</a> tales.</li>
<li>Riley Cooper was created by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;">psul</a></span> in <a href="/scp-3512">SCP-3512</a> where she earned every ounce of rage.</li>
<li>Zoe Smith's music is a selection from Antonín Dvořák's Symphony No. 8 in G major, Op. 88, B. 163, performed by DuPage Symphony Orchestra and conducted by Barbara Schubert and is <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Dvo%C5%99%C3%A1k,_Antonin_%E2%80%94_Symphony_No._8,_Op._88_%E2%80%94_1._Allegro_con_brio.ogg">available under CC from Wikimedia Commons</a>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Thanks&nbsp;to</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=571081&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="qntm" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=571081)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/qntm" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(571081); return false;">qntm</a></span> for not only letting me play in his sandbox but for generously assisting me in building a haunted wing for his castle.<br />
<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/9volt" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2800867&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="9Volt" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2800867)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/9volt" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2800867); return false;">9Volt</a></span> for feedback.<br />
<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2893766&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1527575983" alt="Croquembouche" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2893766)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/croquembouche" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2893766); return false;">Croquembouche</a></span> for helping me with the coding to get the html5 audio player like I wanted it.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Commentary now on <a href="/sirpudding-s-author-page">my author page</a>. The IWT Primer in the Foundation Universe section may also be useful.</p>

